<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193848>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Acroperus tupinamba sp. n. from the type locality. A – B—juvenile females of instar I and II; C – Lparthenogenetic female: C – D—lateral view, E—ventral margin of valevs, F – H—posteroventral corner of valves, I – Jlabrum, K— postabdomen, L—antenna. Scale bars 0.1 mm for A – D, E, L, 0.05 mm for F – K." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193848/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193849>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Acroperus tupinamba sp. n. from the type locality, parthenogenetic females: A – B—lateral view, C—dorsolateral view, D—antero-lateral view, E—major head pres, F—postabdomen, G—postabdominal claw, H—lateral setules of postabdomen, I—antennula and antenna. Scale bars 0.1 mm for A – D, 0.01 mm for F – G, I, 0.002 mm for E, H." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193849/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193850>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Acroperus tupinamba sp. n. from the type locality, appendages of parthenogenetic female: A—antennule, B—limb I, C—ODL and IDL of limb I, D—limb II, E—exopodite of limb II, F—exopodite of limb III, G – H—inner portion of limb III, I—exopodite of limb IV, J—inner portion of limb IV (setules on flaming-torch setae not shown), Kflaming-torch setae of limn IV, L—sensilla of limb IV, M—limb V, N—limb VI. Scale bar 0.05 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193850/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

